    ConstructorNode, DestructorNode

    public class MethodNode
extends InstanceDeclarationNode
    DeclarationNode extension that represents the declaration of a method node type. See decodeStatement(TreeNode, String, Location) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

    • Method Detail

      • getParameterListNode

        public ParameterListNode getParameterListNode()
        The the ParameterListNode that represents the parameters of the method.
        For example:
         public void methodName(int age, String name);
        In the previous statement, the data within the parenthesis are the parameters of the method. The ParameterListNode returned by this method would contain a node for each of the parameter specified, in the correct order from left to right.
        Returns:
        The ParameterListNode that represents the parameters of the method.

      • setExternal

        public void setExternal(boolean external)
        Description copied from class: VariableNode
        Set whether or not the variable is external. A variable is external if it is referenced from a language outside of Fathom. For example, a variable from the C language. Furthermore, a variable is external if it begins with an externally imported C file's name.

        For example: 
         import "externalFile.h";
 
 ...
 
 public static void main(String args[])
 {
        // This is the external variable declaration.
        externalFile.externalType varName;
        
        // This is the external variable assignment.
        varName = externalFile.variableInstance;
 }
        In this example, 'externalFile' is the C header file that is imported. 'variableInstance' is the name of a variable that is contained within the imported header file.
        Overrides:
        setExternal in class VariableNode
        Parameters:
        external - Whether or not the variable will be external.
        See Also:
        VariableNode.setExternal(boolean)

      • generateCSourcePrototype

        public java.lang.String generateCSourcePrototype()
        Generate the C prototype for the method header.

        For example: 
         public void test()
 {
        ...
 }
        will output as "static void test();"

        In essence, this method is just generateCSourceSignature() with a semi-colon attached to the end.
        Returns:
        The C prototype for the method header.

      • generateCSourceSignature

        public java.lang.String generateCSourceSignature()
        Generate the method signature that will appear in the c source output.

        For example: 
         public void test()
 {
        ...
 }
        will output as "static void test()"
        Returns:
        The method signature in the C language.

      • generateCSourceName

        public java.lang.String generateCSourceName()
        Get the name of the method that is output to the C source file.

        For example: 
         package "this/is/my/package";
 
 public class Test
 {
        public void methodName()
        {
                ...
        }
 }
        The output for "methodName()" would look like: "this_is_my_package_Test_methodName()"
        Overrides:
        generateCSourceName in class VariableNode
        Returns:
        The name of the method that is output to the C source file.

      • decodeStatement

        public static MethodNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                         java.lang.String statement,
                         Location location)
        Decode the given statement into a MethodNode instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.
        Example inputs include:
        • public Person findPerson(String name, int age)
        • private int calculateArea(int width, int height)
        • public void doNothing()
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a MethodNode instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a MethodNode.
